With my first group of friends I felt the same way. When I’m with them our personalities just don’t mesh, but I’m not much of a talker either so I never branched out to others groups either. I stuck with them, but never had much to say myself I’d be there for them but never really feel a big part of the group. When I moved schools though I found some really great friends who are much easier to talk to now and I feel more included there. It sucks, but with time you can find people you can truly connect with on a greater level who treat you the same way. Wishing the best for you OP.
It’s a long process so everyone the ding happens it’s hard not to smile with the progress.

Sounds less like a waste of time and more like you grew in that time and that’s amazing. I’m happy for you and hope that you learned more about how to love yourself from this experience. Take care OP.
